gkeyring
========

A small Python tool for shell access to GNOME keyring. It provides simple querying for and creating of keyring items.

Running
=======

You can run the tool directly simply by:

  $ ./gkeyring.py

or by:

  $ python gkeyring.py

(use --help option of course if you don't know this tool yet)

Installation
============

You can also install this tool using distutils [1] or setuptools [2] and have it in your PATH that way.

The recommended way:

  $ easy_install -U gkeyring
  
That will find, download and install the latest available version of gkeyring.

The traditional way of installation is also possible:

  $ python setup.py install

[1] http://docs.python.org/install/index.html#install-index
[2] http://peak.telecommunity.com/DevCenter/setuptools

